From 8c000c961edca59770fa54015e55af3e07a647f5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 20:00:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Expand fact-check: cross-cutting, per-topic, tax validity,
 travel advisories
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the verification dimensions discussed, all grounded in web search with cited URLs.

Cross-cutting (every checked post, returned as `flags`):
- Media authenticity — AI-generated / deepfake / stock / miscaptioned media. The post's
  images are now passed to the fact-check call (config: fact_checking.include_images) and
  comments are included, since fakes/sponsorships/corrections surface there.
- Recycled-as-new, source credibility (satire/parody/known misinfo), undisclosed COI.

Health: dosage & safety, citation integrity (study exists & says that), regulatory
status / recalls / credential checks, correlation-vs-causation.

Finance: scam/fraud red flags, advisor registration (SEC IAPD / FINRA BrokerCheck),
cherry-picked-timeframe / survivorship-bias framing, and TAX VALIDITY — deductions,
write-offs, credits, and tax strategies verified against current IRS rules AND the user's
jurisdiction (config: fact_checking.jurisdiction = Charlotte, NC / North Carolina), since
federal and NC state rules differ.

Political: quote misattribution, satire-as-real, selective editing / missing context,
statistic sourcing.

Travel: location check now also returns `advisories` (authenticity, misrepresentation /
"Instagram vs reality", access/status — closed/permit/seasonal/private, safety/entry).
Also fixes a latent bug: the travel check passed temperature=0, which 400s on opus-4-8
and made every travel check fail silently.

Note rendering: new `flags` block (⚠️ on warnings) and travel advisories render inline
and in the Discord approval embed; fact-check and location results now always appear in
the note, not only via the warning button. Schema additions are back-compatible — claim
entries accept string or {claim, source}; flags/advisories default to empty.

